.TH "batadv_tt_global_is_isolated" 9 "batadv_tt_global_is_isolated" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
batadv_tt_global_is_isolated \- check if a client is marked as isolated
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" batadv_tt_global_is_isolated
.BI "(struct batadv_priv *bat_priv "  ","
.BI "const u8 *addr "  ","
.BI "unsigned short vid "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bat_priv" 12
the bat priv with all the soft interface information
.IP "addr" 12
the mac address of the client
.IP "vid" 12
the identifier of the VLAN where this client is connected
.SH "RETURN"
true if the client is marked with the TT_CLIENT_ISOLA flag, false
otherwise
